# Real-Time Event Analytics Pipeline

a real-time event ingestion and analytics system that tracks and analyzes 
user activity (clicks, searches, purchases) across applications.

# Architecture
User Action → Producer → Kafka → Consumer → Redis (live counters)
                                           → PostgreSQL (permanent storage)
                                FastAPI → reads Redis/DB → serves API

# base logic
- Every user event increments a counter in Redis (INCR user:{id}:count)
- Every 100 events are bulk inserted into PostgreSQL for permanent storage
- FastAPI serves live metrics by reading from Redis

# tech stack
Kafka - event streaming and message queue
Redis - real-time in-memory counters
PostgreSQL - permanent event storage
FastAPI - REST API layer
Docker Compose - runs entire stack with one command

# how to run
docker-compose up

# API endpoints
GET /top-users     → returns top 10 users by event count
GET /user/{id}     → returns event count for a specific user

# learnings
- Event-driven architecture with Kafka producer-consumer pattern
- Redis for real-time counters vs Po
